What I did was take code for a similar example from the Java tutorials.  The code is the KnockKnock client server code from: [Writing the Server Side of a Socket](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/networking/sockets/clientServer.html).  The basic server code is unchanged, I just replaced the console-based client with a JavaFX UI.

Unchanged server code:

 * https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/networking/sockets/examples/KnockKnockProtocol.java

